Program: Outlook
Title: Battling Ebola in Guinea
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p02200j4
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 10 Jul 2014
American doctor William Fischer on his work in Guinea helping victims of the most lethal outbreak of the Ebola virus on record. Also, Indian-born Canadian Kiran Ahluwalia on how she gave up her city career to become an award-winning singer of ghazals. And Sister Gracy, the Indian nun who has devoted her life to providing health care and education in South Sudan. Show less